<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="923" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d923">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-29"><hi rend="italic">November 29,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Eddy reports that no further accurate information in regard to
                            destitution of the Jews and the losses sustained by them can be
                            obtained. No Jews were injured at St. Petersburg and Moscow.)</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>